;At this point, it feels like we’ve all been victims of a cyberattack somewhere, somehow. Data breaches can lay bare the passwords of millions of people, often going undiscovered for years. Which means your identity may be at risk of theft without you even knowing it.
Akka tura, nezmer ad d-nini d akken tḥuzayaɣ akk twaɣir n uẓdam di Inetrent, s wudem neɣ s wayeḍ. Tuffɣa n isefka zemren ad nnalen awalen uffiṛen n yefḍan n yemdanen udiɣ tikwal ara d iseggasen ar zdat ara d-yeffeɣ wawal ɣef aya. Ayagi yemmal-d d akken tamagit inek tezmer ad teffwaɣ neɣ ad tettwakker, war ma teẓriḍ.


;Breaches affected hundreds of millions of accounts in 2013-2016. In December 2016, the biggest breach in history was reported: 1 billion accounts.
Tarewla n isefka tḥuza tiwinas n imilyan n imiḍanen gar 2013 akked 2016. Di Dujambeṛ n 2016, nuder tarewla n isefka meqqren akk deg umezruy: 1 n umelyaṛ n imiḍanen.


